 Walter Investment Appoints Daniel Beltzman to its Board of Directors 
         










    










 






 











 









Walter Investment Appoints Daniel Beltzman to its Board of Directors

Nov 17, 2015, 06:00 ET
		  		  							
						 from   Walter Investment Management Corp. 











 
















































 

 




















 


TAMPA, Fla., Nov. 17, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Walter Investment Management Corp. (NYSE:   WAC) ("Walter Investment" or the "Company") today announced the appointment of Daniel Beltzman, co-founder of Birch Run Capital Advisors, LP ("Birch Run"), to its Board of Directors (the "Board") effective on December 7, 2015. 
"We are pleased Daniel has accepted our invitation to join Walter Investment's Board of Directors. We are firmly committed to enhancing value for all the Company's shareholders, and have maintained a longstanding and constructive dialogue with Birch Run regarding our goals of driving growth and strengthening our business," said Denmar J. Dixon, the Company's Vice Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President. "We welcome Daniel to the Board and look forward to benefiting not only from his financial expertise but also from the perspective he brings as a major shareholder." 
In connection with Mr. Beltzman's appointment, the Company entered into an agreement with Birch Run pursuant to which Birch Run has agreed to vote all of its stock, at the Company's upcoming annual meeting of shareholders, in support of each current Class I director nominated by the Board, and against any shareholder proposals not approved by the Board. The Company also announced that it has amended its existing shareholder rights agreement to permit Birch Run to acquire up to 25% of the Company's outstanding common stock.
The Company also announced that the Board plans to identify and appoint a new non-management director as soon as practicable while working to transition the Board back to its current size of nine directors on or before the 2017 annual meeting of shareholders, consistent with its policy of maintaining a Board with diverse and complementary skill sets and energetic vision to guide the Company's strategic direction.
The agreement between the Company and Birch Run and the amendment to the Company's existing rights plan will be included as exhibits to a Form 8-K to be filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
Daniel Beltzman Biography
Daniel Beltzman co-founded Birch Run Capital Advisors, an investment advisor headquartered in New York City, in 2006.  Birch Run focuses on value-based opportunities in public or private equity or debt securities and looks to stand behind management teams and boards in their efforts to build great businesses and drive long-term shareholder value.  In his current role, Mr. Beltzman oversees the investment portfolio, including formulating investment strategy and generating new investment ideas. Mr. Beltzman currently serves on the Board of Directors of Regis Corporation.  Mr. Beltzman holds a B.B.A and M.Acc. from the University of Michigan. 
About Walter Investment Management Corp.
Walter Investment Management Corp. is a diversified mortgage banking firm focused primarily on the servicing and origination of residential loans, including reverse loans.  Based in Tampa, Fla., the Company has approximately 5,850 employees and services a diverse loan portfolio.  For more information about Walter Investment Management Corp., please visit the Company's website at www.walterinvestment.com.  The information on our website is not a part of this release.
Disclaimer and Cautionary Note Regarding Forward-Looking Statements
